Fusfoo gives today’s high school students a safe, bully-free, educational and engaging space for content to be created, curated, shared and consumed. Changing behaviors like smoking, alcohol abuse, and inactivity could save an estimated $552 billion dollars a year. Now more than ever, individuals and companies recognize the need for behavior change supported by professionals such as health and wellness coaches. These coaches depend on a high degree of continual, personal contact with clients; however, they are limited in both scale and effectiveness by tools available to them today. Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Insight Energy LLC was established to provide acquisition, development, investment and asset management services to financial investors looking for opportunities in the power generation and renewable energy industries. Over the past twenty years, the company or its principals have identified, acquired, co-invested, and managed businesses worth well over $1 billion, including over 2200 MW (equity ownership) of electrical generating facilities, renewable energy production facilities and energy technology businesses. The company is headed by Jeff Grundman and Phil Pickett who have worked together since 1995. They were among the first employees of Rolls-Royce Power Ventures (RRPV), a wholly owned subsidiary of Rolls-Royce plc, created to develop electricity generating companies utilizing Rolls-Royce technology and services. During their seven years at RRPV, Jeff and Phil were instrumental in growing the company from 7 to 130 direct employees and over 300 operations staff at the 20 different power generation companies created around the world. In 2002, Jeff and Phil founded Insight Energy with other partners to develop and acquire mid-size generation projects with financial backing from a major private equity firm. In 2004, with a joint venture partner, they were successful in securing an electricity sales agreement to anchor the development of a green field 580 MW combined cycle power project in Canada. In 2005, Jeff and Phil started working with Stark Investments, a large multi-strategy alternative investment fund management company. While working with Stark, Jeff and Phil founded a team focusing on energy infrastructure investments and subsequently closed and managed over $500m of equity investments in power generation and renewable energy assets.

Full Description: International Institute of Market research and analytics (IIMRA) International Institute of Market Research and Analytics (IIMRA) is the world’s largest market research certification and membership organization. IIMRA, the market leader in market research certification, helps market researchers and consultants to validate their expertise, generate new opportunities for innovation, and stay ahead of the competition.  IIMRA has a rich heritage of grooming young and experienced minds into experts in the vast and deepened field of Market research. IIMRA has grown to become the Gold Standard to which all others are compared in the market research certification. Although not conspicuous to the end consumer, market research helps in designing the products they buy, the price they can pay, the ads they see thus market research is vital in the current market situation. In our long journey in the market research industry, IIMRA has mentored a number of students and market research and analytics professionals, and shaped them to understand, analyze and implement the best practices and capture the potential of the Market Research. IIMRA boosts the credibility of market research and analytics professionals through comprehensive certification IIMRA’s certification programs are designed to help professionals stay ahead of the curve in learning industry best practices Certification programs of IIMRA are offered through remote centers all over the world. IIMRA is led by a team of experienced professionals, known for virtual class rooms and certification programs.  IIMRA offers the following certification courses worldwide: 	Certified Market Research Analyst (CMRA) 	Certified Market Research Professional (CMRP) 	Certified Market Research Specialist (CMRS) 	Certified Market Research Expert (CMRE) 	Data Analysis Certification 	Business Analysis Certification IIMRA inspire research professionals with powerful events and conferences

Full Description: Didage Sales provides refurbished medical equipment to hospitals, surgery centers, and other healthcare facilities. Didage Sales company started in Clunette, IN in 1990 when Chris and Julie Rankin set out to address a specific need within the medical equipment marketplace; access to quality used and refurbished equipment for hospitals, surgery centers and other healthcare facilities. They understand the pressure to find used medical and surgical equipment at an affordable price. They also understand the pressure of wanting to go above and beyond the expectations of the doctors and surgeons who are requesting the equipment.  In 2018, Didage Sales company and Surgical Power merged to expand the sales team, streamline operational processes, organize production data, enhance their quality system and prioritize their team member’s roles while maintaining their trust and support. These processes allow for them to take better care of you, their customer. When you decide to do business with them, you are making the choice to work with a well-established, trustworthy company. They are there to ensure that you are getting the refurbished medical equipment you need, backed up with the knowledge and warranty to ensure you are purchasing what you need for your office.
